# Page Overview Usage

Do not add KPI/overview card rows by default.

Add overview cards only when the page is clearly information-dense, for example:
- 3+ independent datasets/sections users must scan together
- dashboard-style monitoring where quick totals materially improve decisions
- high-volume admin pages where summary metrics reduce navigation time

For simple settings or workflow pages (single primary toggle/form/table), avoid overview cards and keep the UI focused on:
- clear heading + short helper copy
- primary action visibility
- section labels and reduced visual clutter

If unsure, default to **no overview cards** unless the user explicitly asks for them.
